'''''Star Wars Insider'' 39''' is the thirty-ninth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[August]]/[[September]] [[1998]]. Issue 39 features interviews with [[Jake Lloyd]], [[Warwick Davis]], [[Kenny Baker]], and [[Doug Chiang]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk" {{C|by Jon Bradley Snyder}}
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by Dan Madsen}}
*"[[Prequel Profile]]: [[Don Bies]]"
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe]]: [[Caroline Blakiston]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" &ndash; Mara Jade: Who Needs Movies to be a Star? {{C|by [[Bob Cooper]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &ndash; Raising the ''Star Wars'' Flag {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Last Page]]"

===Features===
*"[[Jake Lloyd: Child of the Force]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Nine-year-old actor Jake Lloyd tells Scott Chernoff what it was like to take on one of the most famous roles in film history: the young Darth Vader.</small>
*"[[Terry Brooks: Sword of the Jedi]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>The world-famous fantasy author was just announced as the author of the Episode I novel. In this exclusive interview, Brooks tells Scott Chernoff how he expanded the ''Star Wars'' universe for the Episode I book.</small>
*"[[When Artoo Met Wicket]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>Two of the ''Star Wars'' universe's biggest stars tell the ''Insider'' about their triumphant returns to the ''Star Wars'' sage for Episode I.</small>
*"[[Doug Chiang: From Concept to Screen]]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Episode I's director of design tells David West Reynolds about the challenges of helping to create the look for the new generation of ''Star Wars'' films.</small>

